Bees perform an important role as pollinators for flowers, fruits and vegetables. The warm and moist weather in Yifeng County in China's Jiangxi Province offers eastern honey bees, endemic to China, a sanctuary during the winter months. Watch this episode to find out how the bees cooperate as a team and how they contribute to the survival of plants and other species. About 'Journeys in Nature': Jiangxi Yifeng Series Yifeng County in China's Jiangxi Province is in a subtropical warm and humid climate zone, with an average annual temperature of around 17.2 degrees Celsius. Yifeng is a bamboo home, with nearly a third of its area covered by Moso bamboo forest. For more: Jiangxi Yifeng Series | Ep. 3: Longstipe disanthus Jiangxi Yifeng Series | Ep. 1: In the bamboo woods Jiangxi Yifeng Series | Ep. 2: Hardleaf oatchestnut (Cover image via screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)